# Numeri casuali

``` cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <cstdlib>
#include <ctime>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    srand(time(nullptr));           // just once! (initial seed
                                    // for random numbers)
    for (int i = 0; i < 10; ++i) {
        int r = 1 + rand() % 90;    // random value: 1 <= r <= 90
        cout << r << "\n";
    }
}
```

>

In alternativa (con estremi inclusi): `g2d::randint(1, 90)`

